In Tantra, to focus on Kundalini, one needs a few things going.

1 - Bhuta =
Suddhi. Constant efforts of purification of the various elements that compo=
se the human mind-body structure. In simpler words this translates into mor=
e detachment, more equanimity, more non-reactiveness, control of anger, lus=
t, greed etc etc.

2 - Once and IF a genuine Kundalini awakening happens, o=
ne has to now self identify with the Devata with greater force. Devotion of=
 a far more intense kind is must. The Devata then takes care of the journey=
.

3 - A good guru is very helpful. As Shakti awakens - IF and when it real=
ly does - it can also open up the mind and body to various other things and=
 entities, some of which are not postive in nature while some of them are u=
seless, and given half a chance can make use of the individual for its own =
ends. They take hold of inhernent weakness in character and nature and miss=
-utilizes the same. Hence constant Bhuta-suddhi becomes even more vital.

4=
 - While someday or other every sadhaka will have an experience of Kundalin=
i Shakti awekening and rising up, not all maladies of psychology are becaus=
e of this. The human psychology as understood by west today is puerile and =
insufficient to deal with various things. It is also possible sometimes tha=
t the aura of an individual, which protects us from various subtle influenc=
es and helps us to remain as functional entities, can get "ruptured" due to=
 various reasons, high stress, or unconventional lifestyles, trauma etc. Th=
at can allow free assess of various entities inside the mind and they have =
chances of causing serious havoc. Since all these are very complex and vari=
ous possiblities are there, it is not possible to list down every option. M=
oreover, even if such a diagnosis is correctly done, very few can have the =
right knowledge to rectify the situation. Many who claim they can do so, ar=
e often doing nothing more than an intelligent guess work.
 Sometimes it wi=
