Dear all,=


Just wanted to warn people of kundalini syndrome based on my recent exper=
ience of a patient of mine.

I am doing a psychiatry job at present, and ha=
ve been involved in the care of someone who seems to think she has had a sp=
ontaneous awakening of their kundalini since childhood. This has involved o=
ut-of-body experiences and surges of energy in the body. She is not of Indi=
an origin and had never heard of kundalini until her symptoms started and s=
he searched for an explanation. We have not been able to find anything phys=
ically wrong with her (all tests normal)- so it might be that this is due t=
o deranged kundalini. Many people we call mentally ill describe themselves =
as having a spiritual crisis, or unwanted spontaneous kundalini awakening- =
this has triggered interest and research into this topic in mainstream psyc=
hiatry. Unfortunately these patients are not well-understood by western med=
icine, and as we have no treatments for deranged kundalini, we struggle to =
help them.

Many yogis try to forcibly waken the kundalini. My experience w=
ith this lady confirmed my feeling that kundalini should not be forcibly wa=
kened. This woman wants to kill herself at times because the suffering from=
 the deranged energy is so bad. She feels it will consume her, and it is so=
mething she cannot escape from.

I wondered what solution there could be to=
 her problem. The logical one was to pray to the Divine Mother, who manifes=
ts as the kundalini to relieve the suffering of this woman- and either cure=
 her, or give her the strength to bear this. May I request that the good sa=
maritans among you pray for her, and for others like her (whom we may not k=
now of)- their suffering really is pitiable. 

And let us be careful in our=
 sadhana so as not to end up in this situation ourselves. Perhaps this is w=
hy the bhakti marga is the safest. It is perhaps safest to say "let me be y=
our instrument" and leave the kundalini rising bit to God's will.

Om Dum D=
urgayai Namaha

Aparna 


 
